 THERMAL CROSS SECTION                                            6034 1451
                                                                  6034 1451
 Evaluation, December 2010 by S. F. Mughabghab (BNL)              6034 1451
                                                                  6034 1451
A new evaluation for the thermal, resonance and unresolved regions6034 1451
is carried out for version ENDF/B.VII.1 in order to resolve the   6034 1451
discrepancy between the reactivity worth measurements of Dean et  6034 1451
al.[De07] and ENDF/B.VII.0. An additional objective is            6034 1451
updating the  evaluated file in view of recent resonance          6034 1451
parameter measurements [Ba06] as well as new insights into the    6034 1451
neutron radiative process[Mu10a]-[Mu10b].                         6034 1451
                                                                  6034 1451
The measurements of Dean et al.[De07], which was carried out in a 6034 1451
thermalized neutron spectrum indicated that the capture cross     6034 1451
section of the WPEC file, i.e.ENDF/B.VII.0, is probably           6034 1451
over-estimated. This is due to the fact that paramagnetic         6034 1451
scattering, impurities in the sample and water absorption         6034 1451
in oxide samples were not properly taken                          6034 1451
into account in total cross section measurements to deduce a      6034 1451
thermal capture value. Since the mass-spectra measurements of     6034 1451
Cabell and Wilkens [Ca58] do not suffer from these effects,       6034 1451
a ND-145 renormalized themal capture cross of these authors is    6034 1451
adopted               .                                           6034 1451
